- Removed to_proc_normal (eg &:sym/call) as benchmarks are much better.

Confusing... but better:

```
ints.map { |x| x.to_i } = 27965.7 i/s
strs.map(&:to_i)        = 25309.9 i/s - 1.10x  (± 0.00) slower
ints.map(&:to_i)        = 23740.8 i/s - 1.18x  (± 0.00) slower
strs.map { |x| x.to_i } = 20382.2 i/s - 1.37x  (± 0.00) slower
```

Also removes old RUBY_VERSION checks for variable scoring. Yay!

Closes #74.
